<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.0.0">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://build.university/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://build.university/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2020-03-26T19:25:25+08:00</updated><id>https://build.university/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Build University</title><subtitle>A maker's journey, turned into free education for all.</subtitle><author><name>Kathy Li</name></author><entry><title type="html">How I Built a Startup in One Day</title><link href="https://build.university/news/2020/03/05/building-a-startup-in-one-day/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How I Built a Startup in One Day" /><published>2020-03-05T12:20:15+08:00</published><updated>2020-03-05T12:20:15+08:00</updated><id>https://build.university/news/2020/03/05/building-a-startup-in-one-day</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://build.university/news/2020/03/05/building-a-startup-in-one-day/">&lt;p&gt;Far from being someone who enjoys competing with others, I somehow like to challenge myself a lot.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Merely a day after I got myself out of this “2-Hour Movie Challenge” that I arbitrary created for Leap Day 2020, here I am again, digging another hole for yours truly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But I can explain.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Every time I want to learn (or re-learn) a tech development skill, I like to proceed by building a full-fledged app around it. In fact, this also partly accounts for why I have such a sizable app repertoire for just a one-person dev team.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Earlier today I was hoping to brush up on my PHP.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ergo, once again, a new product ensued.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus began my &lt;strong&gt;“1-Day Startup Challenge.”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Somewhat coincidentally, my tinkering around with my Twitter profile during the movie challenge inspired me to build something that involves check ✅ or cross ❎ marks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One thing leads to another, I built a voting app.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And my initial tech “stack” is super straightforward.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;gmail&quot;&gt;Gmail&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As this experiment would likely require some of the G Suite tools, it made sense to sign up for a new Google account.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;social-media&quot;&gt;Social Media&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With this new email address, I was able to sign up for new &lt;strong&gt;Twitter&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Instagram&lt;/strong&gt; accounts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Handle: “whowouldyouvote”&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also created a new &lt;strong&gt;Facebook Page&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

