&lt;h2 id=&quot;web-app&quot;&gt;Web App&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;or-do-i-really-need-one&quot;&gt;(Or do I really need one?)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is where my approach diverted a little.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The original plan was to build a web application where users can vote on trending topics.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would offer an added benefit for me to practice PHP, which would be used to send vote counts from the front-end back to whatever server I might use.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But as I was signing up for a new Twitter account, it occurred to me that my minimum viable product (MVP) could be further simplified.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In order to launch even quicker for the sake of testing the waters, I wouldn’t even need to build an app from scratch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I could just leverage &lt;strong&gt;Twitter’s built-in poll feature&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means I was literally just minutes away from being ready to launch!&lt;/p&gt;

