&lt;h2 id=&quot;whats-next&quot;&gt;What’s Next?&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This exercise did turn out to be my fastest product launch yet, so I would consider this challenge a small success.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When time allows, I may also see about putting some marketing effort into promoting the site, especially since it is already fully functional and all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Technically speaking though, I only ended up writing very little code for the entire project, which is kind of defeating my original purpose of polishing up my PHP and other skills through hands-on app building.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That being said, I can definitely foresee myself revisiting the project and enhancing it bit by bit —perhaps even turning it into a dynamic app at some point. So I suppose future updates are on the horizon.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Until next time!&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Kathy Li</name></author><summary type="html">Far from being someone who enjoys competing with others, I somehow like to challenge myself a lot.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Welcome to Build University</title><link href="https://build.university/news/2020/02/16/welcome-to-build-university/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Welcome to Build University" /><published>2020-02-16T02:20:15+08:00</published><updated>2020-02-16T02:20:15+08:00</updated><id>https://build.university/news/2020/02/16/welcome-to-build-university</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://build.university/news/2020/02/16/welcome-to-build-university/">&lt;p&gt;Year 2020 has NOT been off to a good start for most of the world, which is why I am now more motivated than ever to squeeze my finite time on Earth to create useful tech.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What I am currently working on, is an app that lets a deaf person communicate with a blind person.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In some ways, this is bringing one of my previous apps* a few steps further.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While I was coming up with a plan to put together living, open-source journals for my 2020 projects, I thought:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;“Why don’t I publish them all to an online blog?”&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus ensued the birth of the Build University website.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;==========&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;*In 2019, I built Listenabel, an interface that reads labels aloud. As a side project, its progress has been slow but steady.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am happy to report that the home stretch is near — for making the app available for public use, including people who happen to be blind or visually impaired.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The project won’t stop there, though. Nor will I.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Kathy Li</name></author><summary type="html">Year 2020 has NOT been off to a good start for most of the world, which is why I am now more motivated than ever to squeeze my finite time on Earth to create useful tech.</summary></entry></feed>